-- Berggruen Seeks Political Help in Karstadt Rent Talks, Handelsblatt Says
-- Oliver Suess
-- 2010-07-05T05:49:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-05/berggruen-seeks-political-help-in-karstadt-rent-talks-handelsblatt-says.html

          
          
             Nicolas Berggruen  may ask the German
government to help him negotiate rent payments for his Karstadt
department stores with the Highstreet partnership,  Handelsblatt 
reported, citing Berggruen in an interview.  
 Berggruen doesn’t want financial state-aid for the
department store, he told the newspaper. Highstreet partnership
owns most of Karstadt’s stores.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
 Oliver Suess  in Munich at 
 osuess@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        